================================================================================
Third-party backends and datasets (OPTIONAL extras — NOT bundled in this repo)
================================================================================

vlatrust's core (src/vlatrust/core, src/vlatrust/report) depends ONLY on numpy
(BSD-3-Clause) and bundles no third-party model code or weights.

The following are reachable only through optional extras. vlatrust imports them
lazily and never redistributes their code or weights. You are responsible for
complying with each upstream license when you install the corresponding extra:

  - OpenVLA (Tier-A token-confidence backend; falsification fixture)
      code: MIT.  weights: per the upstream model card.
  - SmolVLA / LeRobot (datasets + Tier-B backend)
      code: Apache-2.0.
  - openpi / pi0, pi0.5 (Tier-B backend)
      code: Apache-2.0.  Uses Gemma-derived weights governed by the Gemma
      Terms of Use (NOT Apache-2.0). vlatrust bundles NO Gemma weights; the
      [openpi] extra fetches them at the user's discretion and responsibility.
  - ManiSkill / MuJoCo (renderer-heavy perturbation dims, GPU; v0.1.1)
      code: Apache-2.0 / Apache-2.0.

LIBERO-plus (RobustVLA perturbation benchmark, arXiv:2510.00037)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
vlatrust does NOT depend on, import, or redistribute LIBERO-plus. As of
2026-05-28 the LIBERO-plus repository ships NO LICENSE file; absent an explicit
grant it must be treated as all-rights-reserved. vlatrust implements its own
minimal, independently-authored perturbation injector (14 post-hoc dimensions
applied to recorded traces) and does not reuse LIBERO-plus code or assets. If
LIBERO-plus later adds a permissive LICENSE, an optional non-bundling adapter
may be reconsidered.

